parameters: Baby... mine... mine and theirs...\n< Serena >
...In these clothes, even holding you is...\n< Serena >

What should I do... what should I do with this
child...\n< Serena >
It's the second child they forced me to have...\n< Serena >
Even now, I haven't been able to give it a name.\n< Serena >

I just can't do it... It's too frightening, and I
keep running away...\n< Serena >
The third one... all in such a short period...\n< Serena >

To think that something like a healing potion
could be so terrifying. It's a craft that toys
with life. An act that does not even fear God...\n< Serena >

...No, that's not right. There is no sin in
technology. The sin lies with...\n< Serena >
